      <h3>üß† Pharmacology & Neuroscience</h3>
      <div class="pharma-details">
        <h4>Primary Mechanism of Action</h4>
        <p>Meperidine is a synthetic opioid that primarily acts as a Œº-opioid receptor agonist, producing analgesia, euphoria, and respiratory depression. Unlike other opioids, it also has significant activity at sodium channels, NMDA receptors, and monoamine transporters, contributing to its unique side effect profile.</p>
        
